  "prompt": "What does add on item on Amazon mean?",
  "response": "On Amazon, an \"Add-on item\" refers to a product that is typically lower-priced and often small or lightweight, which Amazon can only ship if you meet a minimum order requirement. This is due to the cost inefficiency of shipping these items on their own. \n\nTo purchase an Add-on item, you generally need to have at least $25 of eligible items in your Amazon order. Once you reach this threshold, you can include Add-on items in your order, allowing you to take advantage of their lower prices while still benefitting from shipping efficiency. The Add-on program helps Amazon ensure that these smaller, less expensive items are shipped in a cost-effective way.",
